title: Clifton's Dutch Hill Assoc. holds candidates night
text:
Clifton's Dutch Hill Assoc. holds candidates night October 9, 2015 Last updated: Friday, October 9, 2015, 12:31 AM Clifton Journal Print 
candidates night 
The Dutch Hill Residents Association is hosting a candidate forum for City Council and Board of Education candidates on Thursday, Oct. 15 in the Family Fellowship Church, 78 DeMott Ave. The doors will open at 7 p.m. 
Take this opportunity to speak to the candidates and make your decision. Refreshments will be available. 
For more information, call George at 973-470-0679 or MaryAnn at 973-365-2577. Â© 2015 North Jersey Media Group Tags:
